[Maps of Mexico can be seen at http://www.ezilon.com/maps/images/northamerica/political-map-of-Mexico.gif and https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=5020016,56065. - Sr.Tech.Ed.MJ

It was refreshing to see some of these articles reminding people to vaccinate their animals, including livestock and horses. I also noted ferrets are included in some of these articles.

Sadly, some communities in this update are still not promoting vaccination of pets, even when there are known rabid animals in the area.

It is interesting to see Mexican officials go house to house to investigate vaccination and exposure. Requirements to vaccinate against rabies, record keeping by veterinarians, and sending out reminders are ways they could help decrease the rabies prevalence. For those traveling to resort regions in Mexico, be alert for possibly rabid animals. - Mod.TG]
